[00:56.94]I determined to put the thought of my Time Machine and the mystery of the bronze doors under the sphinx, as much as possible in a corner of memory, until my growing knowledge would lead me back to them in a natural way.  Yet a certain feeling, you may understand, tethered me in a circle of a few miles round the point of my arrival. 
